text=(:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0aStatus: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!{$:Category}]]%0a%0a!Irish%0a%0a:Author: rubyd%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aInformation on the endangered language of Irish (also called Irish Gaelic)%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIrish, also referred to as Irish Gaelic or Gaelic, is listed on Ethnologue as an endangered insular Celtic language native to Ireland (1). Though the language has almost 2,000,000 speakers [note: census reports do not elaborate if this statistic is made up of heritage or second language speakers] , it is still considered endangered as lass than 5%25 of the population is considered frequent speakers (using the language at home) and there are very few families that choose to raise their children with the language (2). %0a%0aHistorically, decline of the language was sparked by the gradual implementation of laws forbidding the Irish language from being spoken under English colonial rule, including The Statute of Kilkenny in 1367 (banned English colonists in Ireland from speaking Irish when interacting with natives), The Statute of Ireland in 1537 (which banned use of Irish in the Irish Parliament), and The Administration of Justice Act in 1737 (which banned use of Irish in the courtroom and forbids completion of legal documentation in Irish) (3). %0a%0aThe Irish government has made several strides towards revitalization of the language, including making it the official language of Ireland, creating Irish Gaelic cultural centers designed to foster cultural traditions within Irish families, and promoting the inclusion of Irish Gaelic in educational programs (2).%0a%0a1. https://www.ethnologue.com/size-and-vitality/gle%0a2. https://rudn.tlcjournal.org/archive/2(4)/2(4)-02.pdf%0a3. https://www.theirishstory.com/2018/10/11/to-extinguish-their-sinister-traditions-and-customs-the-historic-bans-on-the-legal-use-of-the-irish-and-welsh-languages/#.Y1gbmezMK84%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%0aYou must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0a(:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a!!Change article category%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a%0a(:Section: A:)%0a(:Category: EndangeredLanguages:)%0a(:Title: Irish:)
